    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Vibration Damper, Oil Pump, and
        Cooling System - Cleaning, Inspection, and Testing - Gerotor Oil Pump
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Gerotor Oil Pump</title>
        <para>Wash all parts thoroughly in a suitable solvent. Dry with filtered compressed air.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lay front cover assembly on workbench.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect gerotors and housing for nicks, burrs or scoring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace any damaged components.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The inner and outer gerotors are a matched set and cannot be replaced individually.</para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>When installing new gerotors, correct orientation is not required.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>When installing old gerotors, correct orientation is required.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place inner and outer gerotors in oil pump housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000621" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj13/J13029.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Inspect gerotors for wear</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler gauge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front cover assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outer gerotor</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a feeler gauge to inspect for wear by checking the
                <hotlnk document="eges390_255.xml" xrefid="t390001001">radial clearance</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t390001001"/>
                between outer gerotor and oil pump housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000622" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj13/J13030.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Check oil pump end clearance</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler gauge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Straightedge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inner gerotor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outer gerotor</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check oil pump end clearance as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">With the gerotors in place in the front cover, place straightedge across housing.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Insert feeler gauge under straightedge at inner and outer gerotors. Compare end
                    clearance with
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_255.xml" xrefid="t390001001">Specifications
                        <xref refid="t390001001"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If measurements are not within specifications, replace both gerotors (as a set).</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a 12 mm internal hex wrench to remove oil pressure regulator.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000623" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj13/J13031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pressure regulator components</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">End cap and O-ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pressure bypass spring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston poppet</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect oil pressure regulator piston poppet (steel) for binding and sticking due to debris
                or severe piston poppet scoring. Check for a broken oil pressure bypass spring. The spring should
                normally be the only potential cause of any malfunction in this assembly. Replace as necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check regulator bore (aluminum) for severe piston poppet scoring. It should not be expected
                to experience any significant dimensional wear. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="eges390_255.xml" xrefid="t390001001">Specifications
                    <xref refid="t390001001"/>
                </hotlnk>
                . Replace as necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-ring on the end cap.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install regulator components and tighten end cap to
                <hotlnk document="eges390_256.xml" xrefid="e30006b">special torque
                    <xref refid="e30006b"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
